@baseUrl = http://localhost:5104

# =============================================================
# FULL FLOW — AI Scrum Master
# Run requests in order for the complete demo flow
# =============================================================


# -------------------------------------------------------------
# PHASE 1 — DAILY STANDUP
# -------------------------------------------------------------

### [1/8] Clear previous submissions (fresh start)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/standup/submissions
Accept: application/json

###

### [2/8] Tony submits standup — has a blocker
POST {{baseUrl}}/standup/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "memberName": "Tony",
  "yesterday": "Fixed login timeout bug, merged PR #42",
  "today": "Review PR #45, write unit tests for payment module",
  "blockers": "Waiting for vendor API key to test end-to-end payment flow"
}

###

### [3/8] Nam submits standup — no blocker
POST {{baseUrl}}/standup/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "memberName": "Nam",
  "yesterday": "Completed UI design for dashboard",
  "today": "Implement dashboard component",
  "blockers": ""
}

###

### [4/8] Linh submits standup — no blocker
POST {{baseUrl}}/standup/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "memberName": "Linh",
  "yesterday": "Wrote API endpoint /orders",
  "today": "Write unit tests for /orders endpoint",
  "blockers": "none"
}

###

### [5/8] Verify all 3 submissions saved
GET {{baseUrl}}/standup/submissions
Accept: application/json

###

### [6/8] Analyze standup — AI summary + auto-create blocker from Tony
# Expected: summary in English, blockers: ["Tony: Waiting for vendor API key..."]
# A new Blocker record is auto-created in DB for Tony's blocker
POST {{baseUrl}}/standup/analyze
Accept: application/json

###


# -------------------------------------------------------------
# PHASE 2A — SPRINT MONITOR
# Replace YOUR_PROJECT and YOUR_TEAM with actual ADO values
# -------------------------------------------------------------

### [7/8] List available MCP tools
GET {{baseUrl}}/sprint/tools
Accept: application/json

###

### [8/8] Analyze current sprint
# Expected: sprintName, sprintHealth (On Track/At Risk/Off Track),
#           progressPercent, warnings, AI summary in English
GET {{baseUrl}}/sprint/analyze
Accept: application/json

###


# -------------------------------------------------------------
# PHASE 2B — BLOCKER TRACKER
# -------------------------------------------------------------

### List open blockers (Tony's blocker should be here from step 6)
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockers
Accept: application/json

###

### Create a blocker manually
POST {{baseUrl}}/blockers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Dev environment down — cannot deploy",
  "description": "Azure DevOps pipeline fails at build step, infra team investigating",
  "reporter": "Khoi",
  "assignedTo": "Infra Team",
  "sprintName": "Sprint 198"
}

###

### Get blocker by ID (replace 1 with actual ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockers/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Manual follow-up on blocker (replace 1 with actual ID)
# After 2nd follow-up: status auto-escalates to "Escalated"
POST {{baseUrl}}/blockers/1/followup
Accept: application/json

###

### Auto check — follow-up + escalate + AI summary
# Run this daily via Power Automate
# Expected: totalOpen, followedUp[], escalated[], aiSummary in English
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockers/check
Accept: application/json

###

### Resolve a blocker (replace 1 with actual ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/blockers/1/resolve
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resolution": "Vendor provided API key on 19/03/2026. Payment flow tested and working."
}

###

### Verify blocker resolved — should not appear in open list
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockers
Accept: application/json

###

### Get all including resolved
GET {{baseUrl}}/blockers?includeResolved=true
Accept: application/json

###
